# Here we setup actions, which progress in phases. The default phase rules
# will progress an action through the phases automatically.
# 
# Other rules may respond to the action in the different phases, and if they
# consume the fact, they can prevent the action from moving to later phases.
# If they do not consume the fact, then multiple rules may respond to the same
# action.
# 
# The phases are:
# 
# 1. Before
# 2. Instead
# 3. Check
# 4. Carry out
# 5. After

